  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Preparation of RFQ’s</li><li>Source for quotation for materials and service</li><li>Analysis and evaluation of price comparison and costing summary</li><li>Cost planning, estimation and measurement of quantities</li><li>Responsible for main claims, variation orders, budget & cost control</li><li>Prepare settlement for final account</li><li>Manage Contracts administration</li><li>Handle issues including extension of time, terms and condition, loss and expenses claim etc.</li><li>Manage subcon/supplier payment and progress claims</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Quantity Surveying or related field discipline</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant experience in construction industry</li><li>Possess good communication and interpersonal skills to effectively liaise with clients, subcontractors, and project team members</li><li>A problem-solving mindset and the ability to work under pressure to meet tight deadlines</li><li>Work location will be based at the site office in Loyang/ Changi</li></ul><p><br /></p>",
